p.s:
See page 1 of the 'Magisteria' (Add MS 6782 

f. 108
).

Hinc potestates cuiscunque gradus possunt dimidi bisecari; 

vel dimidi in duas partes secundum datam rationem.

Here powers of any degree can be bisected, or divided into two parts according to a given ratio.

Ita Barocius; 

In admirando problemate pag. 93.

Thus Barozzi, in Admirando problemate, page 93.

Let the figures 

nombring the æquall parts beginne at $ k $. & let their numeration runne towards $ f $; 

& the like from $ k $ towards $ g $.

quote.s:
XI.34
 In equal parallelepipedal solids the bases are reciprocally proportional to the heights; 
and those parallelepipedal solids in which the bases are reciporcally proportional to the heights are equal.
